extract_month = lambda x: int(datetime.utcfromtimestamp(int(x)).strftime('%m'))

general_features = list(filter(lambda x: 'general' in x, data.columns))
demographics_features = list(filter(lambda x: 'demographics' in x, data.columns))
genre_features = list(filter(lambda x: 'genre' in x, data.columns))

clean_data = data[general_features]

release_month = data['general release_date'].apply(extract_month)
num_locations = data[[x for x in filter(lambda y: 'locations' in y, data.columns)]].sum(axis=1)
num_countries = data[[x for x in filter(lambda y: 'countries' in y, data.columns)]].sum(axis=1)
num_genres = data[[x for x in filter(lambda y: 'genre' in y, data.columns)]].sum(axis=1)
num_certificates = data[[x for x in filter(lambda y: 'certificates' in y, data.columns)]].sum(axis=1)
num_languages = data[[x for x in filter(lambda y: 'languages' in y, data.columns)]].sum(axis=1)


clean_data['num_locations'] = num_locations
clean_data['num_countries'] = num_countries
clean_data['num_genres'] = num_genres
clean_data['num_certificates'] = num_certificates
clean_data['num_languages'] = num_languages
clean_data['release_month'] = release_month


# clean data
for feature in general_features:
    clean = clean_data[feature] > -1
    clean_data = clean_data[clean]

# 1167609600 == 01/01/2007 12:00AM
clean_data = clean_data[clean_data['general release_date'] > 1167609600]

#cluster_features = list(filter(lambda x: 'rating' not in x and 'votes' not in x and 'genre' not in x, clean_data.columns))
cluster_features = [('general distributors', 'num_certificates')]
for f1, f2 in [('general distributors', 'num_certificates')]:
    cluster_data = clean_data[[f1, f2]]
    # create kmeans object
    num_clusters = 10
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters)

    # fit kmeans object to data
    kmeans.fit(cluster_data)

    # save new clusters for chart
    y_km = kmeans.fit_predict(cluster_data)

    colors = ['red', 'black', 'blue', 'yellow', 'cyan', 'green', 'purple', 'grey', 'orange', 'olive']
    points = clean_data.to_numpy()
    
    cluster_means = list()
    cluster_size = list()
    print('{:<20}{:<10}{:<10}'.format('Mean Rating', '# Series', 'Color'))
    for i in range(num_clusters):
        cluster = points[y_km == i, feature_map['general rating_mean']]
        cluster_means.append(sum(cluster)/len(cluster))
        cluster_size.append(len(cluster))
        print('{:<20}{:<10}{:<10}'.format(sum(cluster)/len(cluster), len(cluster), colors[i]))

    # display the clustering
    plt.figure(dpi=100)
    for i in range(num_clusters):
        plt.scatter(points[y_km == i, feature_map[f1]],
                    points[y_km == i, feature_map[f2]], s=1, c=colors[i])
        plt.title('{} vs {}'.format(f1, f2))
        plt.xlabel(f1)
        plt.ylabel(f2)
    plt.show()
    
    plt.figure(dpi=100)
    _colors = [colors[i] for i in np.argsort(cluster_means)]
    for i in range(num_clusters):
        plt.bar(_colors, sorted(cluster_means), color=_colors)
        plt.title('Cluster Mean Ratings')
        plt.xlabel('Clusters')
        plt.ylabel('Mean Rating')
        plt.ylim((6,9))
    plt.show()
